body:
hi @pranavsharma, I already found OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_VITISAI but my question is how do I fill the arguments. What does it mean each of the parameters?

_In_ OrtSessionOptions* options: I guess this is the options struct as in any other EP.
const char* backend_type: ???
int device_id: I guess is the device id from "xbutil scan"
const char* export_runtime_module: ???
const char* load_runtime_module: ???

I was looking to any kind of "Usage" frame as it is in:

CUDA EP: https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/execution-providers/CUDA-ExecutionProvider.html#cc
ArmNN EP: https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/execution-providers/ArmNN-ExecutionProvider.html#cc

Kind regards.
Sure I did. That is why I am asking. There is no sample code for C++, just for python. Am I missing something?
Yes, we don't have API for C++ currently. The C++ API is just a thin wrapper on top of the C API.

OK, then this chart needs to be updated dimming C++ and C boxes.

![imagen](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60776650/147990361-25c74f3f-b8ff-42e4-899e-6a9f0337a64e.png)

Thanks for your support.
by the way I successfully compiled the library and run onnxruntime_test_all on Xilinx Kria board. You can add it to the list of supported boards.
